{"article_id":"Xu8JvaXscYjaeiIW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell on Capitol Hill","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"( Aaron P. Bernstein/Reuters )","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"If the Republican attempt","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"to repeal and replace Obamacare","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"ultimately fails ,","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"it will be a lesson in the wages of political bad faith .","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"The bill has plenty of obstacles ,","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"including the sheer inertia of the Obamacare status quo and the fact","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"that no one has made the public case for the Republican legislation .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"But the effort also suffers from a mismatch between the longtime public posture of Republicans","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"( Obamacare must and will be fully repealed )","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"and their private misgivings","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"( do we really have to do this , even partially ? ) .","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"It ' s not just that Republicans have said for years","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"that they would repeal Obamacare ;","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"they actually voted to do it .","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"In December 2015 , a bill passed the Senate","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"that was more stringent than the version","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"now struggling for GOP support .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"The 2015 bill only tried to repeal Obamacare","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"( although it fell short of that goal ) ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"while the current bill attempts to repeal and replace ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"i.e. , forge a Republican alternative .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Only two Republican senators voted against the 2015 repeal , Susan Collins of Maine ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"who is still a \" no , \"","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"and Mark Kirk of Illinois ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"who is out of the Senate .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Everyone else was on board ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"and celebrated a righteous blow against Obamacare .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"Winston Churchill said","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that nothing is so exhilarating","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"as getting shot at","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"without consequence .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"For Republicans , nothing was as exhilarating as repealing Obamacare","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"without consequence .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"The repeal bill inevitably got vetoed by President Barack Obama .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"Republican congressional leaders thought","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"they could pick up where they had left off .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"They failed to account for the changed","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"- and more difficult -","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"dynamic with a Republican in the White House","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"ready and eager to sign whatever gets to his desk .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"The prospects of the current bill are clouded by the hesitance of the Medicaid moderates , Republican senators from states","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"that accepted the Obamacare expansion of the program .","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"The legislation is hardly Dickensian on this front .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"It allows states to continue the expansion ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"but , over time , brings the level of federal funding for the new population down to the levels for the rest of Medicaid","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"( years from now , it also establishes a new per capita formula for all of Medicaid ) .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"The 2015 law was tougher on the expansion","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"- it simply ended it after two years -","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"and yet all of today ' s hand-wringers voted for it .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Perhaps they are disturbed by the coverage numbers","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"the Congressional Budget Office has produced about the current bill ?","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"According to the CBO ,","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"it would lead to 22 million fewer people","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"having insurance .","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"But the earlier repeal bill ,","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"per the CBO ,","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"would have led to 32 million fewer people","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"having insurance .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"Perhaps they think","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"the current bill should be more generous ?","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"The fact is the Senate bill","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"unveiled a few weeks ago","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"spends roughly $ 600 billion on replacing Obamacare , or $ 600 billion more than the December 2015 bill .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"It has since been revised","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"to spend even more ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"and scale back the tax cuts .","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"As the publication Health Affairs starkly noted of the 2015 legislation at the time ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"\" it would end the premium tax credits , the cost-sharing reduction payments , the Medicaid expansion , and the small business tax credits","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"- that is , all of the assistance","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"that the ACA gives to low and moderate-income Americans . \"","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"( Rand Paul ,","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"whose shtick is libertarian purity ,","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"is guilty of his own hypocrisy .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"He portrays the 2015 bill as preferable to the current version ,","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"which he opposes","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"for not fully repealing Obamacare regulations .","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"But the 2015 bill didn ' t touch any of the major Obamacare regulations . )","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"All of this is why the Plan B","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"endorsed by President Donald Trump","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"- to revert to a repeal-only bill","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"if the current bill fails -","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"is a non-starter .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"If there aren ' t 50 Republican votes for today ' s relatively generous bill ,","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"there won ' t be 50 votes for anything like what passed a year and a half ago .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Unless , perhaps , Trump promises to veto it ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"and Senate Republicans can consider it once again a blissfully consequence-free vote .","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"If Republicans Do Nothing against Obamacare ,","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"Their Voters Will Punish Them","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":179,"left":95,"right":178,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":95,"left":91,"right":94,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":91,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":93,"right":5,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":93,"left":92,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":92,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":101,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":97,"right":100,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":97,"left":6,"right":96,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":98,"right":99,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":129,"right":176,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":103,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":1